04:05 PM Defendant Roger J Wilson in court with attorney Thomas J. Schneck.  Melissa J. Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases called for plea and sentencing.
State places offer on the record.
Court conducts plea colloquy.

In case 21CM1496:
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Count 2 is Dismissed and read in.

In case 22CM389:
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.
State and Defense make sentencing recommendations.
Defendant makes statement to the court.

In case 21CM1496:
JAIL:  5 days (Credit - 5 days). TIME SERVED;

FINE: $1,229  , includes IID surcharge; 
DNA SURCHARGE:  $200
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $36.05 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to Waukesha County Sheriff's Department. 
*Cash on hand may be applied to Fine.
Payment of Costs/Surcharges/Fine:  To be paid in 90 days. Civil judgment entered as penalty for non payment.

D/L REVOCATION: 12 months;
IGNITION INTERLOCK: 12 months;

Other:  AODA ASSESSMENT AND FOLLOW THROUGH.

In case 22CM389:
Court orders the following:
SENTENCE WITHHELD.

Term of Probation:  1 YEAR; 

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  Court does not object to transfer to Winnebago County if accepted; 

*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores);
*No operation of motor vehicle without a valid driver's licenst; 
*Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel in Waukesha County within 6 months.

COSTS: $243; 
DNA SURCHARGE:  $200;
Defendant to provide DNA sample, within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
*To be paid as a condition of probation.
